HEADWORD: newton
<hw>new"ton</hw> <pr>(n⟦oomac⟧"t'n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Named in
honor of <er>Isaac <ets>Newton</ets></er>. ca. 1900.]</ety> <def>A unit
of force of the Systeme Internationale system of units of measure, equal
to the force that produces an acceleration of one meter per second per
second when applied to a mass of one kilogram. Abbreviated
<altname>N</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
